KineticLawGenerator

public KineticLawGenerator(org.sbml.jsbml.Model model,
                           Properties settings)
                    throws Throwable
Takes a model and settings for kinetic law generation as input, creates a copy of the model, updates the enzymatic catalysis information using the given settings and creates kinetic laws for each reaction in the model copy. The original model remains unchanged.

createKineticLaw

public BasicKineticLaw createKineticLaw(org.sbml.jsbml.Reaction r,
                                        String kineticsClassName,
                                        boolean reversibility)
                                 throws Throwable
Creates a kinetic law for the given reaction, which can be assigned to the given reaction.

Parameters:
r - The reaction for which a kinetic law is to be created.
reversibility - If true this reaction will be set to reversible and the kinetic equation will be created accordingly. If this parameter is false, the reversibility property of this reaction will not be chaged.
kinetic - an element from the Kinetics enum.
Returns:
A kinetic law for the given reaction.

Throwable

storeKineticLaw

public org.sbml.jsbml.Reaction storeKineticLaw(org.sbml.jsbml.KineticLaw kineticLaw,
                                               LawListener l)
This method stores a kinetic law for the given reaction in the currently selected model given by the plugin. The kinetic law is passed as a String to this method. A boolean variable tells this method weather the formula is for a reversible or for an irreversible reaction. Afterwards all parameters within this kinetic law are also stored in the given model. There is no need to call the storeParameters method.

Parameters:
kineticLaw - A string with the formula to be assigned to the given reaction.
l -
